00:01:39.259 --> 00:01:43.509
[Hong Kong, December 7, 1941]

00:01:51.280 --> 00:01:52.420
Hey, Xian, here for yum cha?

00:01:52.420 --> 00:01:53.220
Good morning.

00:02:02.650 --> 00:02:03.340
Xian, here for yum cha?

00:02:03.340 --> 00:02:04.140
Good morning.

00:02:12.330 --> 00:02:14.430
[He Xian,
owner of Hong Kong Huilong Bank]

00:02:14.900 --> 00:02:16.470
-Daddy!
-Daddy!

00:02:16.470 --> 00:02:17.280
Hey,

00:02:18.130 --> 00:02:18.730
good kids.

00:02:19.630 --> 00:02:21.430
Come on, let's enjoy breakfast.

00:02:22.350 --> 00:02:25.470
[Guo Qiwen, He Xian's wife]

00:02:26.829 --> 00:02:27.570
Qiwen.

00:02:28.120 --> 00:02:29.250
You've worked hard.

00:02:30.680 --> 00:02:31.150
Father.

00:02:33.340 --> 00:02:34.020
Have a seat.

00:02:35.300 --> 00:02:36.160
Everyone, sit.

00:02:36.810 --> 00:02:37.870
Go ahead, sit down.

00:02:39.240 --> 00:02:41.100
Father, please have some congee.

00:02:41.250 --> 00:02:41.310
[He Chengxi, He Xian's father]

00:02:41.310 --> 00:02:41.870
Hmm,

00:02:42.350 --> 00:02:43.530
let's eat.

00:02:43.530 --> 00:02:45.280
-Time to eat!
-Dig in!

00:02:45.630 --> 00:02:46.400
Here,

00:02:46.400 --> 00:02:47.660
let me get that for you.

00:02:49.740 --> 00:02:51.270
You must be worn out lately.

00:02:51.570 --> 00:02:52.500
Not tired at all.

00:02:53.060 --> 00:02:53.780
Later,

00:02:54.240 --> 00:02:56.220
you should go home, take a bath,
change into some clean clothes,

00:02:56.220 --> 00:02:57.370
and get some proper rest.

00:02:57.370 --> 00:02:59.440
No need. After yum cha,

00:02:59.440 --> 00:03:01.170
I'll head straight to the pier.

00:03:01.900 --> 00:03:02.740
Daddy,

00:03:03.120 --> 00:03:04.680
are you leaving again?

00:03:05.650 --> 00:03:07.370
Yes, to Macau.

00:03:11.780 --> 00:03:12.460
Xian,

00:03:13.130 --> 00:03:14.930
I'm just afraid of moving again.

00:03:15.120 --> 00:03:18.180
Back in 1938,
when the Japanese invaded Guangzhou,

00:03:18.180 --> 00:03:20.850
our whole family had
to abandon our good business

00:03:20.850 --> 00:03:21.910
and our good home

00:03:21.910 --> 00:03:23.440
to flee to Hong Kong.

00:03:23.970 --> 00:03:26.560
Just thinking
about that time still scares me.

00:03:26.560 --> 00:03:28.490
We've only had a few years of peace—

00:03:28.900 --> 00:03:30.440
must we really uproot everything again?

00:03:30.440 --> 00:03:31.170
Don't worry,

00:03:31.840 --> 00:03:34.440
it's not like we're moving
to Macau right away.

00:03:34.590 --> 00:03:35.850
As the old saying goes,

00:03:36.090 --> 00:03:37.000
"Prepare and you succeed;

00:03:37.000 --> 00:03:38.260
neglect and you fail."

00:03:38.650 --> 00:03:41.680
I'm just going to apply
for a business license in Macau.

00:03:41.680 --> 00:03:43.280
With how uncertain things are now,

00:03:43.280 --> 00:03:45.070
it's not a bad idea to have a backup plan

00:03:45.070 --> 00:03:46.130
for the family.

00:03:49.240 --> 00:03:50.370
You're the head of the household—

00:03:50.370 --> 00:03:51.630
I'll follow your lead.

00:03:54.800 --> 00:03:55.500
Qiwen,

00:03:56.300 --> 00:03:57.940
just put your mind at ease.

00:03:57.940 --> 00:04:00.430
Hong Kong is British territory,
after all.

00:04:01.070 --> 00:04:02.630
And I heard on the radio

00:04:02.940 --> 00:04:05.940
that the Americans are negotiating

00:04:05.940 --> 00:04:07.150
with the Japanese right now.

00:04:07.150 --> 00:04:09.680
So, Hong Kong is a safe place.

00:04:14.180 --> 00:04:15.120
Don't worry.

00:04:15.120 --> 00:04:15.800
Hmm.

00:04:17.570 --> 00:04:18.390
Have some more.

00:04:18.390 --> 00:04:18.950
Hmm.

